  "text": "In contrast, the paleogeographic map during the Bartonian (Fig. 11b ) shows a complete reorganization of the sedimentary landscape, with only detrital and minor mixed sedimentation and a total absence of continuous marine carbonate ramp deposition. A major uncertainty in those paleogeographic maps refers to the connexion between the marine eastern part of the foreland basin and the Jaca basin. But this has no effect on the disappearance of the carbonate platforms and ramps. In the north Pyrenean foreland basin, the sedimentation has been continental since the early Eocene [CITATION_1] .",
